\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. P. oppositifolia} (Pallas) Litv.,{\i  Sched. Herb. Fl. Ross.}{\b  7:} 13 (1911) ({\i P. crassifolia }auct.). Stems 5-40 cm, erect or procumbent, glabrous or pubescent. Leaves up to 40 × 3 mm, very fleshy, obtuse, the upper alternate. Bracteoles obtuse, not deflexed. Perianth-segments 2, glabrous or shortly pubescent, becoming cartilaginous in fruit; stamens 5. {\i S.E. Europe.} Al Rm Rs(W, K, E).
