\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 49.       AMARANTHACEAE}
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  Edit †T.G. Tutin & J.R. Edmondson.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Herbs or rarely small shrubs. Leaves opposite or alternate, entire, exstipulate. Flowers usually hermaphrodite, often in spicate or capitate, usually bracteate inflorescences; bracteoles 2-5. Perianth almost always dry and scarious, usually 4- or 5-merous; segments free or connate at base. Stamens 1-5, opposite the perianth-segments and usually not exserted. Ovary superior, unilocular; ovules amphitropous. Fruit with a membranous, rarely fleshy wall, dehiscing irregularly, or circumscissile (sometimes indehiscent).
\par

