\pard\f0\fs28 Annual, rarely perennial herbs; monoecious or dioecious. Leaves usually alternate. Bracteoles 3-5, small and herbaceous or membranous and spinescent. Perianth-segments 0-5, linear or lanceolate to spathulate. Styles and stigmas 2 or 3. Fruit dry, membranous, indehiscent or dehiscing transversely. Seeds vertically compressed.
